main event: Two civilian observers at The Citadel in Charleston, South Carolina spotted a round, silver object passing overhead at high speed in 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed passing from west to east at an altitude of about 85 degrees, then changed direction to the southeast and disappeared.
A zig-zag motion was noted just before and after the change in the object's course.
The object was observed for about 5 minutes by the naked eye only.
Weather conditions at the time included clear skies, a visible moon, and high thin clouds.
The reporting officer was unable to reach a conclusion about the nature of the object or the reason for its appearance.
